org.fosstrak.reader.rprm.core.mgmt
Class IOPort

java.lang.Object
  org.fosstrak.reader.rprm.core.mgmt.IOPort

public class IOPort
extends java.lang.Object

An IOPort provides the description of the hardware element that provides external input and output lines to connect to other components outside the reader device.

Method Detail

getName

public java.lang.String getName()
Returns the name of this particular IO-port. Since the IO-port names are set by the manufacturer, there is no setName() command.

Returns:
The name of this particular IO-port

getDescription

public java.lang.String getDescription()
Returns a textual description of this IO-port. This is typically used to denote the equipment connected via this IO-port. If no description has been set it returns a String of length zero (an empty string).

Returns:
The description of the IO-port

getAdminStatus

public AdministrativeStatus getAdminStatus()
Returns the administrative status of a particular IO-port. This represents the host's desired status for this IOPort.

getOperStatusAlarmControl

public TTOperationalStatusAlarmControl getOperStatusAlarmControl()
Returns the operStatusAlarmControl attribute of this IO-port. This attribute is the object that controls the conditions for generating alarms alerting a manager of changes in an IOPort's operational status.

Returns:
The alarm control for monitoring the operational status of this IOPort

increaseOperStateSuppressions

public void increaseOperStateSuppressions()
Increases the number of IO port state change notifications that have been suppressed for this IOPort object by 1.
